  "prompt": "What is the remainder when 676767\u2026 unto 900 digit is divided by 999?",
  "response": "The given number consists of the digits 676767..., repeated 300 times to make a total of 900 digits. To find out the remainder when this number is divided by 999, we can use properties of modular arithmetic and patterns in repeating digits. Let's denote the number as \\( N \\).\n\nConsider the clues and steps:\n1. Recognize that 999 is \\( 10^3 - 1 \\).\n2. Break the number into blocks of 3 digits.\n\nSince \\( 676 \\) is repeated throughout the number, we can use:\n\\[ 676 \\equiv 676 \\mod 999 \\]\n\nClearly:\n\n\\[ N = 676676676... (300 times) \\]\n\nThus, each block of three digits, \\( 676 \\), remains constant when modulo 999.\n\nWe need to calculate:\n\\[ \\frac{N}{999} \\]\n\nHowever, recognizing repeating digits, we simplify using modular arithmetic properties:\n\\[ N \\mod 999 = k \\times (676 \\mod 999) \\]\n\nWhere:\n\\[ k = 300 \\]\nand,\n\\[ 676 \\mod 999 = 676 \\]\n\nThus:\n\\[ N \\mod 999 = k \\times 676 = 300 \\times 676 \\]\n\nSimplify the product:\n\n\\[ 300 \\times 676 \\mod 999 \\]\n\nCarry out the multiplication:\n\nFirst, we break it down:\n\\[ 300 \\equiv 300 \\mod 999 \\]\nand\n\\[ 676 \\equiv 676 \\mod 999 \\]\n\nThus:\n\\[ 300 \\times 676 = 202800 \\]\n\nNow simplify \\( 202800 \\mod 999 \\):\nCalculate explicitly:\n\\[ 202800 \\div 999 \\approx 203.003 \\]\n\nFrom here, a simplified calculation reveals:\n\n\\[ 202800 - (999 \\times 203) = 202800 - 202797 = 3 ]\n\nThus:\n\nThe remainder when the number \\( 676676... \\) (900 digits) is divided by 999 consequently is:\n\\[ \\boxed{3} \\]",
